Tana River speaker Nuh Nassir has teamed up with former Garsen MP Danson Mungatana for the governor contest.They have not informed residents on who will run for governor and who will be the running mate. Earlier, both had separately said they will run for governor.The two are perceived as frontrunners in the contest and Governor Hussein Dado may have to seek a coalition of smaller communities if he is to successfully retain the seat.Mungatana and Nassir spoke on Sunday to residents in Bura constituency.Mungatana has been endorsed by his Pokomo community, while Nassir has also been endorsed by his Wardhei community. Both had said earlier that they would be running for the governor seat.Dado is an Orma.